--
-- ORACLE 19c UNIFIED AUDIT GRAMMAR RULES LEARNED:
--   1. ACTIONS and PRIVILEGES cannot be in the same CREATE AUDIT POLICY -- ORA-46383.
--   2. Object actions (ACTION ON schema.obj) cannot mix with system actions -- ORA-46383.
--   3. LOGOFF is not a valid standalone audit action keyword.
--   4. CREATE/DROP PACKAGE BODY are not valid audit keywords; PACKAGE covers both.
--   5. WHENEVER NOT SUCCESSFUL belongs on the AUDIT POLICY (enable) statement,
--      NOT on the CREATE AUDIT POLICY statement -- ORA-00933 if placed on CREATE.
--      Correct pattern:
--        CREATE AUDIT POLICY pname ACTIONS LOGON;
